For this project I had to do 3 full scale POCs and multiple product demos to help the client choose the right BI Platform (which finally was decided in favor of IBM Cognos). To deliver the project I managed a team of 3 Senior and 3 midlevel resources and handed over the project deliverables within defined scope and time.', u'Sr BI Project Manager
BMW - Woodcliff Lake, NJ
September 2012 to December 2012
With the recent upgrade of Cognos from 8.4 to 10.1.1, BMW began to notice problems and outages in peak usage times such as month-end and quarter-end closings. The outages in production environment were having severe business impacts and needed to be addressed immediately.
In this situation, I was tasked to lead the BI team to resolve the problem by thoroughly reviewing the implemented Cognos 10 architecture and processes - including Cognos configuration, Cognos system setting, server configuration and the migration plan/methodology - and identifying a set of recommended actions and systems maintenance plan for immediate and long-term system stability.

At the end of review, I presented my findings to the crisis team headed by the CIO himself
and, upon approval; the recommended changes were implemented immediately. These changes avoided any failure of BI systems during the year-end process -which is considered the peak usage time of the year- and the BI environment is still running without any issues well into the middle of first quarter of this year.

In parallel, I also lead a team of developers to analyze the developmental process including the customizations using SDK, automation processes and solution promotion process in production. This project involved the validation, documentation and setting solution development standards as per industry best practices. We analyzed about 2000 cube views, highlighted the object consumption issue by auditing to capture the usage patterns, introduced a formal testing/QA process and documented the developmental processes. At the end we consolidated over 300 reports and delivered a solution development process/methodology which was approved and is currently followed at BMW.', u"Sr Information Architect

The need was to understand the process flow and then implement the regulations in BI layer. The typical scenario was to detect, calculate and then present claims variations, event and claims closure as per compliance and then to report these out of compliance items using events and alerts to the concerned business personnel. A number of integrated dashboards with the capability of drilling down to the most detailed levels were created as an outcome, and that became the basis for further utilization of BI in sub-areas like online pharmacy and their corresponding government mandated compliance.
